Bibliographic References: PP, no. 362; PPSupp, no. 479; Leroux, pi. 49
Imagery Description: (a) Two nude women, one each side of a laver, on which is a white swan, (b) nude youth with wreath and fillet bending forward in front of seated draped woman holding phiale. Lid: (i) lekanis and (ii) lebes gamikos Non Sepcified female heads. The picture on (a) is framed by reserved bands with triangles at the top corners.
Artist: The Painter of Naples 2585 and his circle
